Case Management System

Overview
--------

The Case Management System is a Django-based web application designed to help users manage and track cases efficiently. It provides tools for organizing case data, handling user roles, and generating reports.

Features
--------

* Case tracking and status updates
* User authentication and role-based access control
* Document and data management
* Report generation
* Responsive UI

Technologies Used
-----------------

Backend:

* Django 4.1.2 – Python web framework for rapid development
* asgiref – Provides ASGI support for asynchronous request handling
* sqlparse – SQL parsing and formatting

Code Quality & Linting:

* Black – Code formatter
* Flake8 – Linter for style and quality enforcement
* Mypy – Type checking for Python

Frontend & Styling:

* Djlint – Django template linter
* CSS & JS Beautifiers – Ensuring clean frontend code

Utilities:

* Click – Command-line interface support
* Colorama – Terminal text styling
* Tqdm – Progress bars for terminal operations
* PyYAML – YAML parsing

Installation
------------

Prerequisites:

* Python 3.x installed
* Virtual environment setup (optional but recommended)

Steps:

1.  Clone the repository:

    ```bash
    git clone [https://gitlab.com/Melipo/case-management-system.git](https://gitlab.com/Melipo/case-management-system.git)
    cd case-management-system
    ```

2.  Create and activate a virtual environment:

    ```bash
    python -m venv venv
    source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use venv\Scripts\activate
    ```

3.  Install dependencies:

    ```bash
    pip install -r requirements.txt
    ```

4.  Apply database migrations:

    ```bash
    python manage.py migrate
    ```

5.  Run the development server:

    ```bash
    python manage.py runserver
    ```

6.  Open `http://127.0.0.1:8000/` in your browser.

Usage
-----

* Users can create and manage cases.
* Role-based access control ensures secure case management.
* Reports can be generated for case analytics.

